Notes:
* Any Ace + Face Card = Blackjack
* BlackJack for player results is a 3:2 payoff
* In case of tie, player loses (except when player has a blackjack)
* Doubling down is only offered when player has enough cash
* Split is offered when the player has two same-valued cards (irrespective of suite)
* If the player goes bust, he loses the bet (even if the dealer goes bust in the same round).
* The program shows the appropriate total (hard or soft) in case of player.

Execution:
* Extract Blackjack.tar.gz
* All files should be in the same directory 
* Main.rb is included, which should be executed as "ruby Main.rb"

Other Notes
* Sample Main.rb simulates one round of play on the table with multiple players
